I find myself retreating more and more from Instagram, do you feel the same? The more it attempts to keep me logged on, making direct messages easier, changing the algorithms, the more I want to just grow my own ‚Äòother‚Äô channels and remind myself of what I set out to do in the online world originally. I feel a change in the air from other accounts I respect as well (cc @candicebrathwaite , @livpurvis). This is my first full week at work since having Peggy! I‚Äôm not going to lie, juggling full-time work without childcare for the last 10 months has been a struggle. We‚Äôve relied on babysitting apps, taken it in turns to get emails done, I‚Äôve cried a lot, and more recently we moved Peggy to one day a week at nursery. I get asked all the time why I didn‚Äôt take more time off and that I deserved a longer break but the realities of being freelance become real when you have a child. Most people assume that one of you will go back to work and leave the other with the baby - but neither one of us could pay our mortgage alone and the state allowance wasn‚Äôt enough as only the female is entitled - Chris as a freelancer wasn‚Äôt entitled to anything.  I am thankful everyday that I do a job I love and can work around my child as much as possible but I know that nursery, just a few days a week, will allow me to get my work done and spend more quality time with my daughter not on my phone. And she bloody loves it. (Jeans were part of a paid project I worked on with Gap a few months ago. I have worked with Arket before but I bought this cardigan).

I never wore red lipstick until a few years ago as I had always read that it was ‚Äòtoo much going on‚Äô with frames and I didn‚Äôt wear glasses on my wedding day. But now I‚Äôm in my 30s, I am so much more settled in myself and how I‚Äôm perceived to the world, I really couldn‚Äôt care less and no longer pander to someone else‚Äôs view of what is ‚Äòattractive‚Äô. Most days I wear glasses, some days I wear contacts for something different, but it‚Äôs for nobody else but myself ü§ì.

I thought it was maybe a good time to re-introduce myself: hi üëãüèº I‚Äôm Alex. I was a Fashion Editor and worked in the fashion industry and on mags for the last 14 years. I started my blog because 7 years ago there wasn‚Äôt anyone speaking to me on my ¬£16k a year job. As I‚Äôve grown, the blog has grown too and now, Frugality means so much more and is a community of likeminded people who understand that life isn‚Äôt always having the most expensive things and knowing when to spend money and when to save. I work with my husband and we muddle through co-parenting with our little gizmo baby called Peggy who cracks us up daily.  I didn‚Äôt include my face on Instagram until a few years ago because in all honesty my glasses and wonky teeth got no engagement but nowadays I simply care less. I eat way too much KFC. I love lists but get anxious when I can‚Äôt tick anything off most days. I should probably stop tagging my outfits as most of what I wear is old (case in point). I love Tate Britain and Francis Bacon but I also love Australian Love Island. We bought a house in London because no one else wanted it but have now turned it into something marvellous. Nice to meet you and thanks for following along üòò

You might have noticed we've been a bit quiet on house updates lately...money restraints have taken their toll lately and we're regrouping to save before starting again. This house was the top of our budget in its condition, there was no contingency pot or extra money for refurbishments. In fact, we've just remortgaged to pay back money borrowed for the works so far and for once, enjoying being debt-free and not in our overdrafts. My feed is always about aspiration, but behind the images I'm always in the real world and think it's important to share the highs and the lows. We love this house but sometimes living in a makeshift kitchen with mould up the walls gets us down...but we know it will be worth it in the end. We're also not beating ourselves up about not getting anything done this month - this weekend we've been watching Harry Potter back to back and it's just the weekend we needed üëåüèº
